<br>
I agree that you should have just tagged along with there raid and got the ball if it dropped (I doubt any warrior in an uber guild would want epic, since it blows).   There is a decent chance that it wouldn't have dropped.  In this case, by going along you would have learned some valuable lessons about how to do Fear.<br>
<br>
As far as the suggestion that you make a deal with them, I doubt that would work.   1) competiton is pretty tight an many servers.  If another &quot;uber&quot; guild found out that CT was up, they might just start heading into Fear and not care about the deal you worked out.  2) by the sounds of it, you guys would have probably taken forever to clear fear.   As a member of a semi-uber guild, I think we would just start clearing once 8-10 people showed up and just keep clearing as others show up.  By the time we get a full raid force logged on and into Fear, the zone will be mostly clear.  We would probably be able to clear the zone twice as fast as a newb guild.<br>
