<br>
After the initial raid decided that the raid had been blown by the uber guild, I organized a rag-tag group of people to go up and work with them to get a chance at armor/epic drops.<br>
<br>
Draco trained on camp twice during the next 45 mins, possibly due to the actions of some of the first-timers. I was asked to take my people out of the plane, and I did so. I asked to be sent tells on any epic items, and over the course of the next hour, two golem balls and two shaman tears were given to the original raid.<br>
<br>
The guild feels bad about running over the raid that was forming. They apologized for it on their website, and even used it as ammunition for booting someone out of their guild that they needed a reason for.<br>
<br>
I play in a lot of different zones that inspire competition. It is always hard at the beginning to watch someone do that to your raid.<br>
<br>
What you need to do is allow it to teach you some important lessons: motivation, mobilization, negotiation and communication.<br>
<br>
If you walk away with that in mind, it might just be the most successful fear raid you ever went on.<br>
<br>
My 2 cp.<br>
